Rating: 4
I doubled the recipe and changed things up a bit: I chopped the garlic in a food processor, then added the lime, salt, and olive oil. Additionally I added a good handful of chopped cilantro. I then marinated skirt steak, organic chicken breasts, and a swordfish steak for about four hours. The chicken was amazing, the brightness of the lime came through, but wasn't overpowering - I had used a little extra lime. The swordfish was also quite good - originally I had planned to use sea scallops and think that would be even better. Unfortunately, I thought the steak was just OK. (I will try to follow the recipe if I do it again.) The steak was tender, but not as flavorful as I had hoped. The steak definitely needed an extra spritz of lime at the end, as the lime flavor got lost in the grilling. I'm giving the recipe four forks because I can't wait to have the leftover chicken for lunch.

