Rating: 4
This is one of my favorite dishes. Here in the desert it's better known as Carne Asada. We marinate the steak in lime, garlic, and cilantro over night, then grill it fast over a hot mesquite pit the next day. For three pounds of skirt steak you had better use one lime - rolled until it's softened, a dozen large cloves of garlic - crushed and diced, and about one quarter cup of chopped cilantro leaves. Eat with Pico Pica or Pico de Gallo sauce, not a vinegar based pepper sauce.

